The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, April 07, 2004 				 More time for FM fee
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, April 6: The Telecom Regulatory Authority of India (Trai) has recommended that private FM radio broadcasters could be given the option of deferring the payment of the next installment of licence fees till a decision is taken on the fee structure and the mode of payment.																								In an interim report, the telecom regulator has also stated that the government will have the authority to collect the license fees along with interests from due date. 																								The recommendations followed five private FM broadcasters meeting with the deputy Prime Minister, L. K. Advani. 
